docs.abstract: Such an action would seek to block a technical integration of WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger and Instagram, people familiar with the matter said.
docs.snippet: Such an action would seek to block a technical integration of WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger and Instagram, people familiar with the matter said.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The Federal Trade Commission is considering seeking a preliminary injunction against Facebook to prevent the social network from integrating several of its messaging services, according to three people with knowledge of the matter.

headline.main: F.T.C. Is Said to Consider an Injunction Against Facebook
headline.print_headline: F.T.C. Poised to Resist Plan To Link Facebook Platforms

byline.original: By Mike Isaac and Cecilia Kang

docs.abstract: The commission took aim last month at the Chinese tech giant’s sales to telecom carriers in rural America.
docs.snippet: The commission took aim last month at the Chinese tech giant’s sales to telecom carriers in rural America.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHENZHEN, China — Huawei, the Chinese technology powerhouse, is suing the Federal Communications Commission for choking off its sales in the United States, the latest in the besieged company’s widening efforts to hit back at regulators and critics across the globe.

headline.main: Huawei Sues the F.C.C., Ramping Up Fight With Critics and Foes
headline.print_headline: Huawei Sues F.C.C., Widening Fight With Regulators

docs.abstract: Oscar Munoz will leave the role in May and be succeeded by J. Scott Kirby, the company’s president.
docs.snippet: Oscar Munoz will leave the role in May and be succeeded by J. Scott Kirby, the company’s president.
docs.lead_paragraph: Oscar Munoz, who helped to steady United Airlines after a troubled 2010 merger, but not without the occasional public relations crisis, will step down next year as the airline’s chief executive.

headline.main: United C.E.O. Munoz to Step Down, 5 Years After Leading Turnaround
headline.print_headline: He Turned United Around, And Now His Work Is Done

docs.abstract: A federal court ruling is a victory for House Democrats who are investigating President Trump’s relationship with the German bank.
docs.snippet: A federal court ruling is a victory for House Democrats who are investigating President Trump’s relationship with the German bank.
docs.lead_paragraph: A federal appeals court said Tuesday that Deutsche Bank must turn over detailed documents about President Trump’s finances to two congressional committees, a ruling that will most likely be appealed to the Supreme Court.

headline.main: Trump Loses Appeal on Deutsche Bank Subpoenas
headline.print_headline: President Loses Appeal on Deutsche Bank Subpoenas, but It’s Not the Last Word

docs.abstract: In its first safety report, the ride-hailing company detailed sexual assaults, murders and fatal crashes through its platform.
docs.snippet: In its first safety report, the ride-hailing company detailed sexual assaults, murders and fatal crashes through its platform.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber said on Thursday that it had reports of 3,045 sexual assaults during its rides in the United States in 2018, with nine people murdered and 58 killed in crashes, in its first study detailing unsafe incidents on the ride-hailing platform.

headline.main: Uber Says 3,045 Sexual Assaults Were Reported in U.S. Rides Last Year
headline.print_headline: Uber Offers Rare Window Into Its Safety Record

docs.abstract: Shari Redstone gets her wish, bringing about the merger of two media giants in a $25 billion deal. The plan is to become a content arms dealer in the streaming wars.

docs.abstract: The video app said it would review its policies after a 17-year-old in New Jersey who discussed Chinese detention camps was locked out of her account.
docs.snippet: The video app said it would review its policies after a 17-year-old in New Jersey who discussed Chinese detention camps was locked out of her account.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — The video app TikTok on Wednesday reversed its decision to block an American teenager who posted a clip in which she discussed the mass internment of minority Muslims in China, and acknowledged that its moderation system had overreached in shutting her out of her account.

headline.main: TikTok Reverses Ban on Teen Who Slammed China’s Muslim Crackdown

docs.abstract: The indie distributor Neon has Oscar contenders with Bong Joon Ho’s latest and the documentary “Apollo 11.”
docs.snippet: The indie distributor Neon has Oscar contenders with Bong Joon Ho’s latest and the documentary “Apollo 11.”
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — It was not a surprise that critics would love “Parasite,” the latest film from the acclaimed director Bong Joon Ho. But box-office success for this sometimes funny, sometimes horrifying Korean-language tale of economic inequality was no sure thing. Enter Tom Quinn, the head of Neon, a rising independent film distributor and production company.

headline.main: ‘Parasite’ Has Shocked the Box Office, Helped by an Upstart Studio
headline.print_headline: The Upstart Indie Studio With an Eye for Success

docs.abstract: Many people joining the newsroom are digitally savvy and helping media with a digital transition, says Theodore Kim, who runs fellowships and internships.

docs.lead_paragraph: How do New York Times journalists use technology in their jobs and in their personal lives? Theodore Kim, director of newsroom fellowships and internships, discussed the tech he’s using.

headline.main: A Big Screen to Sift Through Recruits
headline.print_headline: Keeping Track of 5,000 Applicants to The Times
